title: Leadership Coup Rumours Swirl Around British PM Keir Starmer | 10 News+
description: UK Prime Minister Sir Keir Starmer’s government is in crisis, as rumours swirl of an internal plot to oust him as leader of the Labour Party. One of the frontbench MPs named as being behind the ‘planned coup’, Health Secretary Wes Streeting, has publicly denied it. And now the embattled PM has been forced to deny that his own office was responsible for starting the rumours. title: Experts Warn Artificial Intelligence Will Lead To Human Extinction | 10 News+
description: Two experts on artificial intelligence have delivered a terrifying warning - that AI will lead to the extinction of humanity, possibly in our lifetime, if something isn’t done to stop its harm. The authors of the new book ‘If Anyone Builds It, Everyone Dies’ say that if AI becomes smarter than humans, it could develop its own goals, deceive its creators, and gain power over us all. They are telling governments to act quickly, to stop the development of ‘super AI’. title: Five Chinese Tourists Dead After Minibus Crashes Into Ravine In Bali | 10 News
description: At least five Chinese tourists have died and eight others were injured after their rental minibus plunged into a shallow ravine on Bali on Friday.  The group of 13 was travelling from Denpasar to Buleleng in northern Bali when the crash occurred.  Authorities said the driver swerved to avoid a collision with another car but lost control, sending the vehicle off the road. title: Trump Says He Will Sue BBC For Up To $5 Billion Next Week | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump has told reporters he will take legal action against the British Broadcasting Corporation next week. Speaking aboard Air Force One, Trump said he would sue the BBC for anywhere between $1 billion and $5 billion over a documentary his lawyers called defamatory. He accused the broadcaster of creating “fake news”, saying, “They actually changed the words coming out of my mouth.” On Thursday, the BBC issued a personal apology to Trump but maintained there is no legal ground for him to take action. title: Trump Says MRI Result Was ‘Best Doctor Had Ever Seen’ | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump has told reporters his MRI results from his recent physical were “the best result” his doctor had ever seen. When asked by a reporter on Air Force One why he had an MRI, Trump said it was part of his physical and admitted he has “no idea what they analyse, but whatever they analyse, they analysed it well,” claiming he has “as good a result as they’ve ever seen.” Earlier this week, the White House declined to provide specific details of the medical images from Trump’s physical last month but said the exam showed he was in exceptional health. title: Former Spanish FA President Luis Rubiales Egged At Book Launch In Madrid | 10 News
description: Former Spanish Football Federation president Luis Rubiales was egged at the launch of his new book in Madrid on Thursday. Rubiales said the attack was carried out by his uncle, "who is a troublemaker and always has been". "He came in with some eggs and threw them at me, but I didn't know what he had in his hands, and when I saw him burst in, I thought he was carrying a gun," he told Radio MARCA. In February, Spain's High Court found Rubiales guilty of sexual assault for kissing forward Jenni Hermoso without her consent during Spain’s 2023 Women’s World Cup victory celebrations in Sydney. He was ordered to pay a fine of more than 10,000 euros and was banned from football for three years by FIFA.
